it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-sept-24-2019/|title='Black-ish' and 'The Voice' adjust up, 'New Amsterdam' adjusts down: Tuesday final ratings|last=Welch|first=Alex|work=TV by the Numbers|date=September 25, 2019|accessdate=September 25, 2019}}</ref>\n| end6             = \n| endrating6       =\n| season6          = 2019\u201320\n| rank6            = \n| viewers6         = \n| 18_49_rating6    =\n\n}}\n\n===Critical response===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"float: right;text-align:center;margin:20px\"\n|-\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\" colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" | Season\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\" colspan=\"2\" | Critical response\n|-\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\" | [[Rotten Tomatoes]]\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\" | [[Metacritic]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#25181F;\"|\n| ''[[Empire (season 1)|1]]''\n| 84% (49 reviews)\n| 69 (39 reviews)\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#FFF4BF;\"|\n| ''[[Empire (season 2)|2]]''\n| 87% (35 reviews)\n| 77 (22 reviews)\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#C0A03D;\"|\n| ''[[Empire (season 3)|3]]''\n| 87% (32 reviews)\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#3D4144;\"|\n| ''[[Empire (season 4)|4]]''\n| 83% (6 reviews)\n| \n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#3D4144;\"|\n| ''[[Empire (season 5)|5]]''\n| 83% (6 reviews)\n| \n|-\n|}\n\n''Empire'' has received positive reviews from critics. The praise has gone towards the cast, particularly Howard and Henson.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/showtracker/la-et-st-cookie-lucious-how-taraji-p-henson-and-terrence-howard-built-an-empire-20150319-story.html |title=Cookie & Lucious: How Taraji P. Henson and Terrence Howard Built an 'Empire' |date=March 19, 2015 |work=latimes.com}}</ref>\nOn [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the first season has a rating of 84%, based on 49 reviews, with an average rating of 7.24/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/empire/s01/|title=Empire: Season 1|date=January 7, 2015|work=rottentomatoes.com}}</ref> The site's critical consensus reads, \"Though heavy on melodrama, ''Empire'' elevates the nighttime soap with its top-notch cast, musical entertainment, and engrossing plots.\"<ref name=rottentomatoes>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/empire/s01/|title=Empire: Season 1|date=January 29, 2015|publisher=|accessdate=January 8, 2015}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]] the show has a score of 72 out of 100, based on 39 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/tv/empire-2015|title=Empire (2015)|work=Metacritic|accessdate=January 29, 2015}}</ref> For the second season, the score rose a few points higher, further praising the performances of Henson and Howard, the character development, plot development, and the show's self-awareness for being a soap opera. On Rotten Tomatoes, the second season has a 87% \"Certified Fresh\" with an average rating of 7.54/10 from critics and a score of 77 from Metacritic, indicating \"generally positive reviews\".\n\n[[David Wiegand]] wrote in the ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'': \"Almost nothing about ''Empire'', created by Lee Daniels (''[[The Butler]]''), feels original, but after a few minutes, you will stop caring\".<ref>{{cite news |url=http://seattletimes.com/html/television/2025339152_empirefoxxml.html|title='Empire' rocks on Fox, clich\u00e9s and all|accessdate=December 30, 2014|date=December 29, 2014|newspaper=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |via=[[The Seattle Times]] |last=Wiegand |first=Dave}}</ref> [[50 Cent]] stated via [[Twitter]] that he feels that ''Empire'' is being marketed by FOX in a way that resembles the marketing for the 2014 [[Starz (TV channel)|Starz]] series that he produces called ''[[Power (TV series)|Power]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2036414/50-cent-empire-power-fox-beef/|title=50 Cent's Latest Beef Is With A New Fox TV Show|accessdate=December 30, 2014|date=December 29, 2014|work=[[MTV News]]|publisher=Viacom Media Networks|last=Fleischer|first=Adam}}</ref> [[Michael Logan (journalist)|Michael Logan]] of ''[[TV Guide]]'' described ''Empire'' as a \"sudsy retooling of ''[[King Lear]]'' with hip hop as the backdrop and praised Henson for her portrayal of the character Cookie.<ref name=TVG123114>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/empire-fox-lee-daniels-1091355.aspx|title=Lee Daniels Builds a Soapy New Hip-Hop Empire for Fox|date=December 31, 2014|first=Michael|last=Logan|authorlink=Michael Logan (journalist)|accessdate=January 3, 2015|work=[[TV Guide]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]}}</ref>\n\nThe show's premiere ranked as Fox's highest-rated debut in three years. Viewership has increased continuously; ''Empire'' is the first primetime broadcast series in at least 23 years to have its viewership increase week to week for its first five episodes.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bibel|first1=Sara|title=FOX's 'Empire' Is The Only Primetime Broadcast Series To Grow In Viewers in Each of its First 5 Telecasts in at Least 23 Years|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/02/06/foxs-empire-is-the-only-primetime-broadcast-series-to-grow-in-viewers-in-each-of-its-first-5-telecasts-in-at-least-23-years/360518/|accessdate=February 6, 2015|work=TV by the Numbers|publisher=Tribune Digital Ventures|date=February 6, 2015}}</ref> The show continues to increase its viewership with further episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/style-blog/wp/2015/02/26/this-is-tv-history-empire-continues-to-rise-in-the-ratings-and-nothing-ever-rises-in-the-ratings/|title=This is TV history: 'Empire' keeps rising in the ratings \u2014 and nothing EVER rises in the ratings|last=Yahr|first=Emily|work=[[The Washington Post]]|publisher=Nash Holdings LLC|date=February 26, 2015|accessdate=February 26, 2015}}</ref> Episodes of the show have also been heavily watched on Video on Demand and other streaming services.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Steel|first1=Emily|title='Empire' May Provide Fox the Big Hit It Needs|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/28/business/media/empire-may-provide-fox-the-big-hit-it-needs.html|accessdate=January 28, 2015|work=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=The New York Times Company|date=January 28, 2015}}</ref> As of its first season finale, ''Empire'' has now surpassed ''[[The Big Bang Theory]]'' as the highest rated scripted program in the 2014\u20132015 television season. The first season finale is also the highest rated debut season finale since May 2005, when ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'' ended its first season. ''Empire's'' season one finale grew 82 percent from its series premiere, making it the show that has grown the most over the course of its first season since ''[[Men in Trees]]'' during the 2006\u20132007 season.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bibel|first1=Sara|title=TV Ratings Wednesday: Updated -'Empire' Finale Soars to Huge Series High, 'Arrow', 'Supernatural' & 'CSI: Cyber' Down|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/03/19/tv-ratings-wednesday-empire-finale-soars-to-huge-series-high-arrow-supernatural-csi-cyber-down/376814/|accessdate=February 6, 2015|work=TV by the Numbers|publisher=Tribune Digital Ventures|date=March 19, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size\\\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominee(s)\n! Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=32|2015\n|[[American Film Institute]]\n|[[American Film Institute Awards 2015|Top 10 TV Shows]]\n|''Empire''\n|{{won}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=3|[[BET Awards|BET Award]]\n| rowspan=2|[[BET Award for Best Actor & Actress|Best Actor]]\n| [[Terrence Howard]]\n|{{won}}\n| rowspan=3|<ref name=\"2015BETNoms\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-juice/6568770/bet-awards-2015-nominations|title=BET Awards 2015 Nominations: Chris Brown & Nicki Minaj Lead|last=Mitchell|first=Gail|publisher=[[Prometheu